    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How much is this?' (for male objects)"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'How much is this?' for a masculine noun, use قَدِّيش هاد؟ (addaysh haad?). قَدِّيش means 'how much/how many', and هاد is 'this' (masculine).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "قَدِّيش هاد؟",
            "english": "How much is this? (masc.)",
            "transliteration": "addaysh haad?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How much is this?' (for female objects)"
        },
        "text": "For a feminine noun, you'd ask قَدِّيش هادِي؟ (addaysh haadi?). هادِي is 'this' (feminine).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "قَدِّيش هادِي؟",
            "english": "How much is this? (fem.)",
            "transliteration": "addaysh haadi?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "The Word 'Price'"
        },
        "text": "The word for 'price' is سِعر (se'er). You can use it when talking about the cost of something.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "سِعر",
            "english": "Price",
            "transliteration": "se'er"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "ما هو السِّعر؟",
            "english": "What is the price? (more formal)",
            "transliteration": "ma huwwa as-se'er?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
