    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Basic Numbers for Prices (1-3)"
        },
        "text": "When stating prices, you'll often use numbers. Let's learn one, two, and three: وَاحِد (waaḥed - one, masc.), وِحْدَة (weḥdeh - one, fem.), تْنَيْن (etnayn - two), تْلاتة (tlaate - three).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "وَاحِد / وِحْدَة",
            "english": "One",
            "transliteration": "waaḥed / weḥdeh"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "تْنَيْن",
            "english": "Two",
            "transliteration": "etnayn"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "تْلاتة",
            "english": "Three",
            "transliteration": "tlaate"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Smallest Currency Unit: Piaster/Qirsh"
        },
        "text": "The smallest unit of currency in many Levantine countries is the 'Piaster' or 'Qirsh'. The singular is قِرْش (qirsh), and the plural is قُروش (qroosh).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "قِرْش",
            "english": "Piaster/Qirsh (singular)",
            "transliteration": "qirsh"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "قُروش",
            "english": "Piasters/Qirsh (plural)",
            "transliteration": "qroosh"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Stating a Full Price"
        },
        "text": "To state a full price, you'd combine numbers, the main currency, and the smaller unit. For example: خَمْس لِيرات وخَمْس قُروش (khams leeraat w khams qroosh - five Liras and five Piasters).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "خَمْس لِيرات وخَمْس قُروش",
            "english": "Five Liras and five Piasters",
            "transliteration": "khams leeraat w khams qroosh"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "الكِتاب سِعرو تلات لِيرات.",
        "english": "The book's price is three Liras.",
        "transliteration": "el-kitaab se'ro tlaate leeraat."
      },
      "context": "Using a number and currency unit."
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "عندي قِرْش واحد.",
