    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Saying 'It costs...' / 'Its price is...'"
        },
        "text": "To say 'It costs...' or 'Its price is...', you use سِعْرو (se'ro) for masculine objects and سِعْرها (se'erha) for feminine objects. The 'o' and 'ha' are possessive suffixes for 'its'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "سِعْرو خَمْس لِيرات.",
            "english": "Its price is five Liras (masc.).",
            "transliteration": "se'ro khams leeraat."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "سِعْرها خَمْس لِيرات.",
            "english": "Its price is five Liras (fem.).",
            "transliteration": "se'erha khams leeraat."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "The Word 'Discount'"
        },
        "text": "The word for 'discount' is خَصْم (khaSm). You might also hear تَنْزِيلات (tanzeelaat) which means 'sales' or 'discounts'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "خَصْم",
            "english": "Discount",
            "transliteration": "khaSm"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "تَنْزِيلات",
            "english": "Sales / Discounts",
            "transliteration": "tanzeelaat"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
