        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'Is there a discount?'"
        },
        "text": "To ask if there's a discount, you can say: فِي خَصْم؟ (fee khaSm?). فِي means 'there is/are' or 'is there/are there?'",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "فِي خَصْم؟",
            "english": "Is there a discount?",
            "transliteration": "fee khaSm?"
          }
